  <article class="relative min-h-screen flex items-start px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-32 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto w-full">
      <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center text-slate-400 hover:text-indigo-400 mb-8 transition-colors">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"/>
        </svg>
        Back to Blog
      </a>

      <header class="mb-12">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-indigo-500/20 border border-indigo-500/30 rounded-full text-xs text-indigo-300">Ruby</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-indigo-500/20 border border-indigo-500/30 rounded-full text-xs text-indigo-300">Static Sites</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-indigo-500/20 border border-indigo-500/30 rounded-full text-xs text-indigo-300">Web Development</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-4">
          <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-400 to-purple-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
            Getting Started with Static Site Builders
          </span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-slate-400 text-lg">
          <%= Date.new(2024, 1, 15).strftime('%B %d, %Y') %>
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="apple-glass p-8 prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Static site generators have revolutionised how we build websites. They offer the perfect balance between simplicity and power, allowing developers to create fast, secure, and maintainable sites without the overhead of traditional content management systems.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Why Static Sites?</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Static sites are pre-rendered HTML files that can be served directly from a CDN. This means:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-slate-300 space-y-3 mb-8 list-disc list-inside">
          <li>Lightning-fast load times</li>
          <li>Enhanced security (no server-side vulnerabilities)</li>
          <li>Cost-effective hosting</li>
          <li>Version control friendly</li>
          <li>Easy to deploy and scale</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Choosing the Right Tool</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          The static site builder landscape is diverse. From Jekyll and Hugo to custom Ruby solutions, each tool has its strengths. When choosing, consider:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-slate-300 space-y-3 mb-8 list-disc list-inside">
          <li>Your preferred programming language</li>
          <li>Template engine flexibility</li>
          <li>Build time and performance</li>
          <li>Community and ecosystem</li>
          <li>Deployment options</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Getting Started</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Starting with a static site builder is straightforward. Most tools follow a similar pattern:
        </p>
        <ol class="text-slate-300 space-y-3 mb-8 list-decimal list-inside">
          <li>Install the generator</li>
          <li>Create your project structure</li>
          <li>Write your content in markdown or templates</li>
          <li>Build and deploy</li>
        </ol>

        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Whether you're building a personal blog, documentation site, or portfolio, static site generators provide a solid foundation for modern web development.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

